6) Pattern Matching In Constraints	
====================================

- We are saying that in email it shud be amir@gmail.com [If it will not have ‘@‘ and ‘.’ Then It will Throw an Error]


CREATE TABLE users (
user_id INT,
username VARCHAR(50), 
email VARCHAR(100) CHECK (email LIKE ‘%@%.%’)
);


INSERT INTO users (user_id, username, email) VALUES (1, 'Amirs', 'amir@gmail.com');

[Query OK, 1 row affected (0.001 sec)]




INSERT INTO users (user_id, username, email) VALUES (1, 'Adnans', 'adnangmail.com');

[ERROR 3819 (HY000): Check constraint 'users_chk_1' is violated.]




INSERT INTO users (user_id, username, email) VALUES (1, 'Ahmedk', 'ahmed@gmailcom');

[ERROR 3819 (HY000): Check constraint 'users_chk_1' is violated.]








