7) End_Date Should be Greater Than the Start_Date 
===================================================

We have a Projects Table In which we have Project Start_Date & End_Date But we know that the Start_Date should be Always Less Than the End_Date, So we can put a Check Constraint for this.

[Greater Than Symbol is >]
[Less Than Symbol is <]


CREATE TABLE projects ( 
project_id INT, 
project_name VARCHAR(100), 
start_date DATE, 
end_date DATE, 
CHECK (end_date > start_date) 
);




- We are Inserting a Record which has a Start Date which is 1-Jan-2023 & End Date 31-Dec-2023 which is Perfect
INSERT INTO projects (project_id, project_name, start_date, end_date) VALUES (1, ‘Project Alpha’, ‘2023-01-01’, ‘2023-12-31’)




- We are Inserting a Record which has a Start Date which is 1-Jan-2023 & End Date 31-Dec-2022 This will Throw an error as it is Violating the Check Constraint
INSERT INTO projects (project_id, project_name, start_date, end_date) VALUES (1, ‘Project Alpha’, ‘2023-01-01’, ‘2023-12-31’)






